No, not directly. From the jQuery API docs:<p>$(&quot;#dataTable tbody&quot;).on(&quot;click&quot;, &quot;tr&quot;, function(event){
  alert($(this).text());
});<p>In Minified, the easiest way to get exactly the same event handler is this:
$(&quot;#dataTable tbody&quot;).each(function(tbody) {
  $(&#x27;tr&#x27;, tbody).on(&quot;click&quot;, function(){
    alert($(this).text());
}, tbody);
